reviewText: Sooo..well done and edgy to bring out the message of just because you are a star your life isn't perfect or easy.  However, what does a stars selfishness offer their friends and others - maybe at least some respect.  What can the star and/or the new friend do for you to make you a better person.  Looking into ones life may help some of you who thing you are a star - at home, school, or wherever see how you are treating others around you.  Do they love you, fear you, jealous of you, or hurtful and mean?  This move was awesome with the way the handled the subject.  I watch it frequently just because it is a great clean family movie.

reviewText: This is a clean, sweet film with a great soundtrack. Even the background music is sweet and soothing to listen to. It's a great family film, and although some of the dialog is corny, it's still enjoyable and a refreshing change from the overtly sexed-up or violent films that studios insist on making. Aaron Carter is cute as the pop star J.D. but I got a kick out of seeing former child pop stars David Cassidy and Leif Garrett in supporting roles. Clever casting all around.
summary: Clean, Cute, Adorable with great soundtrack
